Look at this nice little snippet:

``` gdscript
func empty_if():
    if something:

func test():
    print("test1")

    else:

func test():
    print("test2")
```

It allows you not only to define the same function twice without giving any error but also the function is considered undefined if you try to call it (and if you _don't_ call it, the game actually runs without problems).

My guess is that the `if` statement should expect an indented block afterwards (the same way `func` works) but it's not happening somehow.
